      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kevinsawicki/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kevinsawicki/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kevinsawicki/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kevinsawicki/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kevinsawicki/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": true
    },
    "created_at": "2017-05-17T21:22:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-05-17T21:22:33Z",
    "body": "> Does making the boolean something like overrideWebViewSecurityFeature make your concern less worrysome?\r\n\r\nSo if we go with an option that simply enables or disables it, like `webviewTag`, then apps that don't use the `<webview>` tag at all can set it to `false` and Electron will require two less files at startup and set less globals which seems nice."
  },
